<TITLE> Over 100 BDR men held in Cox's Bazaar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Cox's Bazaar, May 13 (bdnews24.com)One hundred border guards were arrested on Wednesday at the 17 Rifles Battalion headquarters on sedition charges filed after the Feb 25-26 mutiny at the BDR headquarters in Dhaka, police said. Sub-inspector Ahsan Ullah of Cox's Bazaar Model Police Station said they made the arrests at 9am. Ullah said, the arrested Subedar Ashraf Ali, Subedar Major Abu Taher, Naib Subedar Nasir Uddin and 99 other paramilitary troops were immediately handed over to the district jail authorities through the intervention of the court. They have been accused of engaging in sabotage activities in Cox's Bazaar in the wake of the BDR revolt. SI Abdullah Al Mamun, second officer of the police station, filed the sedition case on May 6 against the BDR men, he said. Mamun said the arrested BDR men have been accused of charges under Bangladesh Penal Code sections 120, 121, 121 (KA) and 120 (KHA). Major Mohammad Tanim Hossain, operations officer, 17 Rifles Battalion, confirmed that 100 men had been detained on Wednesday. bdn
